API : Application Programming Interface 


FrontEnd     Request                        Backend                  Database
Browser         =>     API Call    =>       Server        <=>        Database
React JS        <=                 <=       Node JS                  MySQL / Mongo
                                Response

API Call can be sent through 4 HTTP Methods 
1. GET 
        Request:
            API URL *
            Headers * 
            HTTP Method * 
            URL Parameters
        Response 
            Status Code *
            Response Data *
2. POST 
        Request:
            API URL *
            Headers * 
            HTTP Method * 
            Request.Body *
        Response:
            Status Code *
            Response Data *
3. PUT
        Request:
            API URL *
            Headers * 
            HTTP Method * 
            URL Parameters * 
            Request.Body * 
        Response:
            Status Code *
            Response Data *
4. DELETE
        Request:
            API URL *
            Headers * 
            HTTP Method * 
            URL Parameters *
        Response:
            Status Code *
            Response Data


200 - 299 : Success
400 - 499 : Client side error 
500 - 599 : Server side error 

200 : OK 
201 : Created 
400 : Client Side Error
401 : Unauthorised 
404 : Page not Found / Forbidden 
500 : Internal Server Error 

Interview Question 
Authorisation vs Authentication 

SOAP API 
Parses XML Data 

REST API 
Parses JSON Data 